1
00:01:51,469 --> 00:01:53,494
<i>My dear children...</i>

2
00:01:53,604 --> 00:01:56,801
<i>...it is now better than several years...</i>

3
00:01:56,908 --> 00:01:59,069
<i>...since I moved to New York...</i>

4
00:01:59,177 --> 00:02:01,873
<i>...and I haven't seen you
as much as I would like to.</i>

5
00:02:03,481 --> 00:02:07,508
<i>I hope you will come
to this ceremony of papal honors...</i>

6
00:02:07,618 --> 00:02:09,518
<i>given for my charitable work.</i>

7
00:02:11,989 --> 00:02:15,425
<i>The only wealth in this world is children.</i>

8
00:02:15,526 --> 00:02:21,505
<i>More than all the money,
power on earth you are my treasure.</i>

9
00:02:23,701 --> 00:02:26,033
<i>Anthony and Mary...</i>

10
00:02:26,137 --> 00:02:30,969
<i>...although I entrusted your education to
your mother for your own best interests...</i>

11
00:02:31,042 --> 00:02:33,533
<i>...you know how I look forward to seeing you...</i>

12
00:02:33,644 --> 00:02:36,704
<i>...and to a new period of harmony in our lives.</i>

13
00:02:38,149 --> 00:02:43,119
<i>Perhaps you might prevail upon your mother
to come to this celebration...</i>

14
00:02:43,221 --> 00:02:45,746
<i>...and that from time to time...</i>

15
00:02:45,857 --> 00:02:49,657
<i>...we can all see each other at family functions.</i>

16
00:02:49,761 --> 00:02:54,425
<i>Anyway, I remain, your loving father.</i>

17
00:03:24,095 --> 00:03:26,325
Hail Mary, full of grace...

18
00:03:30,201 --> 00:03:32,192
...blessed art thou amongst women...

19
00:03:33,571 --> 00:03:37,667
...and blessed is the fruit of thy womb, Jesus.

20
00:03:37,775 --> 00:03:43,078
Holy Mary, mother of god
pray for us sinners...

21
00:04:06,671 --> 00:04:10,298
...almighty god, bless the insignia...

22
00:04:10,311 --> 00:04:12,901
...of Saint Sebastian the martyr.

23
00:04:12,910 --> 00:04:17,310
That it may contribute to the sacredness of him...

24
00:04:17,415 --> 00:04:19,349
...to whom it is given.

25
00:04:31,762 --> 00:04:33,662
Do you, Michael...

26
00:04:33,764 --> 00:04:38,992
...promise to be faithful to the noble purposes of this order...

27
00:04:39,036 --> 00:04:44,064
...to have a special care for the poor,
the needy and those who are ill?

28
00:04:44,141 --> 00:04:45,938
I do so promise.

29
00:05:00,925 --> 00:05:04,292
May the blessing of almighty god...

30
00:05:04,395 --> 00:05:09,355
...father, son, and holy spirit...

31
00:05:09,467 --> 00:05:15,001
...descend upon you and remain with you forever.

32
00:05:15,006 --> 00:05:16,633
Amen.

33
00:06:48,466 --> 00:06:51,824
Vincent, our name's not on the list.

34
00:06:53,571 --> 00:06:54,868
Write it in.

35
00:06:54,972 --> 00:06:57,463
Mancini. M-A-N-C-I-N-I.

36
00:06:59,243 --> 00:07:01,971
- Hey, is there a problem here?
- No problem, our name's not on the list.

37
00:07:01,979 --> 00:07:04,413
Hey, you're not on the list, you'll have to leave immediately.

38
00:07:04,515 --> 00:07:06,813
- There's no two ways about it!
- You want to dance with me sir?

39
00:07:06,917 --> 00:07:09,913
Joe! Joe! It's Vinnie.
Vinnie, it's Okay, these are our guests.

40
00:07:10,454 --> 00:07:11,853
Sorry Dave.

41
00:07:11,956 --> 00:07:14,857
- It's all right.
- Hey Vinnie. Welcome to the party.

42
00:08:07,778 --> 00:08:09,177
It's good to see you.

43
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:12,147
It's good to see you again.
This is my husband.

44
00:08:12,249 --> 00:08:14,149
This is my son, Anthony.

45
00:08:15,252 --> 00:08:18,153
The order of Saint Sebastian
is one of the highest honors...

46
00:08:18,255 --> 00:08:20,390
...the Catholic Church can bestow upon a layman.

47
00:08:20,391 --> 00:08:23,189
The award was first granted by Pope Gregory...

48
00:08:23,294 --> 00:08:26,229
What about Mr. Corleone's connections
with las Vegas gambling?

49
00:08:26,330 --> 00:08:28,762
Press kits have pictures of...

50
00:08:28,766 --> 00:08:30,927
What about his involvements with the underworld?

51
00:08:31,035 --> 00:08:32,502
Hey, cut the crap, huh?

52
00:08:32,603 --> 00:08:35,868
The Pope, the holy father himself...

53
00:08:35,973 --> 00:08:40,679
...has this very day blessed Michael Corleone.
You think you know better than the Pope?

54
00:08:40,778 --> 00:08:42,678
- Do it, do it.
- Vincent!

55
00:08:42,780 --> 00:08:45,180
- Yes?
- She loves you.

56
00:08:50,287 --> 00:08:51,777
- What'd he say?
- I love you too.

57
00:08:57,895 --> 00:09:01,422
Hi, Vincent.
I remember you.

58
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:04,124
You remember me?
From where?

59
00:09:04,235 --> 00:09:08,645
- From the last time we had a party together.
- Did you come down to the club?

60
00:09:08,739 --> 00:09:11,230
- No, it was a wedding.
- A wedding?

61
00:09:12,343 --> 00:09:15,835
I was eight, and you were 15.

62
00:09:15,946 --> 00:09:18,972
Well I, I had a lot of girlfriends when I was 15.

63
00:09:19,083 --> 00:09:21,578
- Eight-year-olds?
- Especially eight-year-olds.

64
00:09:23,420 --> 00:09:25,547
Where's Mary?

65
00:09:25,656 --> 00:09:28,056
Would somebody please hail Mary?

66
00:09:28,159 --> 00:09:30,354
Excuse me, your excellency.

67
00:09:30,461 --> 00:09:33,496
You know, you haven't kissed me hello yet.

68
00:09:33,497 --> 00:09:36,825
- Relatives always kiss.
- Oh, now we're related?

69
00:09:36,834 --> 00:09:39,259
I'm your little cousin.

70
00:09:46,277 --> 00:09:48,006
Who's your father?

71
00:09:48,112 --> 00:09:50,808
I'll give you a hint.

72
00:09:50,915 --> 00:09:53,440
- He's Italian.
- Mary.

73
00:09:53,551 --> 00:09:56,418
Mary, we've been waiting for you.

74
00:09:56,520 --> 00:10:00,513
Remember - remember now, keep your voice low, right?

75
00:10:00,624 --> 00:10:03,149
And smile! Don't forget to smile.

76
00:10:20,878 --> 00:10:24,809
Carissimi Amici, the honorary chairman...

77
00:10:24,815 --> 00:10:29,879
...of the Vito Corleone Foundation, my daughter, Mary Corleone.

78
00:10:39,563 --> 00:10:40,830
Thanks.

79
00:10:42,199 --> 00:10:47,675
I don't think I inherited my father's
love for speech making, but here it goes.

80
00:10:48,839 --> 00:10:53,439
The Vito Corleone Foundation helps
the impoverished of every country,...

81
00:10:53,544 --> 00:10:58,344
...gives grants to artists, funds medical research,...

82
00:10:58,449 --> 00:11:03,182
...and is particularly dedicated
to the resurrection of Sicily.

83
00:11:03,287 --> 00:11:05,619
ArchBishop Gilday...

84
00:11:05,723 --> 00:11:10,160
...here is $100 million for the poor of Sicily...

85
00:11:10,261 --> 00:11:12,456
...in the name of Vito Corleone.

86
00:11:12,563 --> 00:11:15,361
Don't spend it all in one place.

87
00:11:36,954 --> 00:11:39,081
Mary - Mary, I'm so proud of you.

88
00:11:45,164 --> 00:11:50,700
- Michael, you've done a wonderful thing for Sicily.
- ...a special surprise from Las Vegas;...

89
00:11:50,701 --> 00:11:54,728
Well, let's just hope the money gets to the people who need it.

90
00:11:54,838 --> 00:11:58,604
<i>- Amen.
- ...the most important part,...</i>

91
00:11:58,709 --> 00:12:00,943
<i>Johnny Fontane!</i>

92
00:12:09,586 --> 00:12:11,349
Thank you very much.

93
00:12:11,455 --> 00:12:14,356
I'm happy to be here with you,
and I'd like you to join me...

94
00:12:14,458 --> 00:12:18,387
<i>...in honoring commendatore Michael Corleone.</i>

95
00:12:22,533 --> 00:12:25,934
And I have something special for our host and Godfather:

96
00:12:26,036 --> 00:12:28,561
I just happen to know his favorite song.

97
00:12:28,672 --> 00:12:30,606
Michael, where are you going?
It's your favorite song.

98
00:12:30,708 --> 00:12:34,144
I'm off here to the kitchen
to hear some Tony Bennett records.

99
00:12:35,879 --> 00:12:38,211
<i>It's your favorite song.
It's "Sausage" His Own.</i>

100
00:12:38,315 --> 00:12:40,146
<i>That's right; a Sausage Sandwich!</i>

101
00:12:40,250 --> 00:12:41,683
I'll be back.

102
00:12:46,023 --> 00:12:48,924
<i>A rose must remain</i>

103
00:12:49,026 --> 00:12:51,586
<i>with the sun and the rain</i>

104
00:12:51,695 --> 00:12:56,496
<i>or its lovely promise won't come true</i>

105
00:12:57,668 --> 00:13:00,432
<i>to each his own</i>

106
00:13:00,537 --> 00:13:04,667
<i>to each his own</i>

107
00:13:04,775 --> 00:13:08,370
<i>and my own is you</i>

108
00:13:16,120 --> 00:13:18,145
Hello, Kay.

109
00:13:27,965 --> 00:13:31,059
Well congratulations, Michael, that's really quite an honor.

110
00:13:31,168 --> 00:13:34,103
It's a little expensive, wouldn't you say?

111
00:13:36,774 --> 00:13:38,708
Cake?

112
00:13:38,809 --> 00:13:40,470
No, thank you.

113
00:13:54,124 --> 00:13:57,025
- It's been a long time, hasn't it?
- Uh huh. Yeah.

114
00:13:57,127 --> 00:13:59,527
- Eight years.
- Yeah.

115
00:13:59,630 --> 00:14:01,530
You look wonderful.

116
00:14:05,302 --> 00:14:07,668
Your son has something
he wants to talk to you about.

117
00:14:07,771 --> 00:14:10,103
I came here for him.

118
00:14:12,576 --> 00:14:14,476
Nice to see you.
Thank you.

119
00:14:18,882 --> 00:14:21,715
<i>If a flame is to grow</i>

120
00:14:21,819 --> 00:14:25,186
<i>there must be a glow</i>

121
00:14:25,289 --> 00:14:27,883
<i>to open each door</i>

122
00:14:27,991 --> 00:14:30,721
<i>there's a key</i>

123
00:14:30,828 --> 00:14:33,695
<i>I need you, I know</i>

124
00:14:33,797 --> 00:14:36,425
<i>I can't let you go</i>

125
00:14:44,374 --> 00:14:47,434
- What's wrong with being a lawyer?
- Nothing, except he doesn't want it.

126
00:14:47,544 --> 00:14:50,445
He loves music, he wants his life to be in music.

127
00:14:51,815 --> 00:14:54,215
Well, music is great. I love music.

128
00:14:54,318 --> 00:14:56,718
But he should finish what he started.

129
00:14:58,088 --> 00:15:01,421
- I'm going my own way.
- Your own way?

130
00:15:01,525 --> 00:15:03,152
- Professional singer?
- That's right.

131
00:15:03,260 --> 00:15:06,696
And what happens -- what happens if you fail?

132
00:15:06,797 --> 00:15:08,731
I won't fail.

133
00:15:08,832 --> 00:15:11,164
- Men always believe that.
- I know.

134
00:15:11,268 --> 00:15:15,178
If you have a law degree you're taking out insurance.

135
00:15:15,272 --> 00:15:17,397
After that you can do whatever you want.
You can work for me...

136
00:15:17,407 --> 00:15:21,602
I will never work for you. I have bad memories.

137
00:15:23,981 --> 00:15:26,609
Every family has bad memories.

138
00:15:30,420 --> 00:15:32,513
I will always be your son...

139
00:15:32,623 --> 00:15:37,185
...but I will never have anything
to do with your business.

140
00:15:37,294 --> 00:15:43,282
- Anthony, finish the law degree.
- No.

141
00:16:00,817 --> 00:16:05,151
Well, that he got from you. That "no".

142
00:16:07,958 --> 00:16:13,165
- You could have helped me to convince him, Kay.
- Oh, convince him of what?

143
00:16:13,263 --> 00:16:15,731
Of what?

144
00:16:15,832 --> 00:16:20,696
He throws his life away.
He throws greatness away.

145
00:16:21,738 --> 00:16:24,707
This is greatness?

146
00:16:24,808 --> 00:16:26,808
You know Michael, now that you're so respectable...

147
00:16:26,810 --> 00:16:29,176
...I think you're more dangerous than you ever were.

148
00:16:29,279 --> 00:16:33,687
In fact, I preferred you when you were just a common Mafia hood.

149
00:16:34,554 --> 00:16:40,521
- Kay, now can we talk common sense here?
- All right. - Okay.

150
00:16:47,331 --> 00:16:50,300
Tony knows that you killed Fredo.

151
00:16:56,573 --> 00:16:59,940
- What did you come here for?
- I came here to protect my son.

152
00:17:00,043 --> 00:17:02,637
I didn't come here to see you disguised by your church.

153
00:17:02,746 --> 00:17:05,146
I think that was a shameful ceremony.

154
00:17:09,419 --> 00:17:12,217
I spent my life protecting my son.

155
00:17:12,322 --> 00:17:16,524
I spent my life protecting my family!

156
00:17:16,526 --> 00:17:19,227
Let's be reasonable, Okay?

157
00:17:19,329 --> 00:17:23,129
That's your big thing, isn't it, Michael?

158
00:17:23,233 --> 00:17:27,397
Reason backed up by murder.

159
00:17:27,504 --> 00:17:29,165
Oh, God.

160
00:17:30,440 --> 00:17:35,870
- God, you hate me. You hate me.
- No, I don't hate you.

161
00:17:37,114 --> 00:17:38,513
I dread you.

162
00:17:42,919 --> 00:17:46,355
I did what I could, Kay, to protect...

163
00:17:46,456 --> 00:17:49,518
...all of you from the horrors of this world.

164
00:17:50,527 --> 00:17:52,427
But you became my horror.

165
00:18:02,205 --> 00:18:04,537
The children still love you though.

166
00:18:04,641 --> 00:18:06,336
Especially Mary.

167
00:18:09,046 --> 00:18:10,604
That's something.

168
00:18:13,150 --> 00:18:16,984
We can build on that, for their sake.

169
00:18:20,757 --> 00:18:22,384
Let's try.

170
00:18:22,492 --> 00:18:25,723
Only if you let Tony go free to have his own life.

171
00:18:26,830 --> 00:18:28,156
Away from you.

172
00:18:35,205 --> 00:18:37,105
I'll let Tony go.

173
00:18:39,609 --> 00:18:41,236
Thank you.

174
00:19:19,816 --> 00:19:21,750
You could hurt somebody with those.

175
00:19:23,153 --> 00:19:25,121
You've been working too hard, let me show you around.

176
00:19:25,222 --> 00:19:27,588
Can you get me an interview
with Michael Corleone?

177
00:19:27,691 --> 00:19:30,558
Uh, no. I'm a relative but I can't do that.

178
00:19:30,660 --> 00:19:33,288
What else could I do for you?

179
00:19:33,397 --> 00:19:35,991
- Handsome but useless.
- Oh, yeah?

180
00:19:36,099 --> 00:19:39,296
- That's okay. I'll gamble.
- You like to gamble?

181
00:19:39,403 --> 00:19:43,430
Why don't we go to Atlantic City?
My town. I'll show you how to gamble.

182
00:19:43,540 --> 00:19:46,106
Yeah, but I like to win.
How will I know what numbers to pick?

183
00:19:46,109 --> 00:19:47,972
Do I look okay like a guy who's gonna lose?

184
00:19:47,978 --> 00:19:49,368
Well...

185
00:19:51,782 --> 00:19:54,216
...that's a spooky-looking guy there.

186
00:19:54,317 --> 00:19:57,844
What's a guy like that doing
at Michael Corleone's house?

187
00:19:57,954 --> 00:20:00,786
- That's Joey Zasa's bulldog.
- You know that guy?

188
00:20:00,790 --> 00:20:02,517
Yeah, I know that guy.

189
00:20:02,626 --> 00:20:05,527
That guy's name is Anthony Squigliaro.

190
00:20:05,629 --> 00:20:07,563
They call him "The Ant."

191
00:20:07,664 --> 00:20:10,997
He dips his bullets in Cyanide.

192
00:20:19,142 --> 00:20:20,905
Don Altobello.

193
00:20:22,546 --> 00:20:26,346
- I come to pay my respects.
- Grazie.

194
00:20:29,453 --> 00:20:31,887
You honor my family's friendship.

195
00:20:31,988 --> 00:20:37,949
- Where is my goddaughter? Constanzia...
- Don Altobello...

196
00:20:38,829 --> 00:20:44,095
It was not so long ago
I held you in these old hands.

197
00:20:46,096 --> 00:20:47,096
Michael...

198
00:20:48,572 --> 00:20:51,200
No, no.
I stand. I stand.

199
00:20:51,308 --> 00:20:56,744
Michael, I lost all the venom all the juice of youth.

200
00:20:56,847 --> 00:21:02,482
I lost the lust for women and now my mind is clear.

201
00:21:02,586 --> 00:21:05,487
My duty to God is clear.

202
00:21:05,589 --> 00:21:08,990
I - I have a special favor to ask.

203
00:21:10,660 --> 00:21:14,892
Can I attach my name...

204
00:21:14,998 --> 00:21:20,799
...to the Vito Corleone Foundation
so that you and I can be joined...

205
00:21:20,837 --> 00:21:23,533
...in name and spirit?

206
00:21:25,876 --> 00:21:27,571
One million dollars.

207
00:21:33,717 --> 00:21:38,151
- Godfather.
- Don Altobello, you have such a heart.

208
00:21:40,657 --> 00:21:44,285
Come, let's go and sample some of Italy, old vino.

209
00:21:51,501 --> 00:21:54,993
The Vatican knows nothing of these shareholders.

210
00:21:55,105 --> 00:21:58,506
Good.
I have a tendency to worry.

211
00:21:58,608 --> 00:22:02,666
We've increased our position
substantially and naturally, I worry.

212
00:22:02,779 --> 00:22:04,406
Come along now.
Stop worrying.

213
00:22:04,514 --> 00:22:06,914
We have an agreement.

214
00:22:07,017 --> 00:22:09,679
Good. How do you think I got this grey hair?

215
00:22:09,786 --> 00:22:11,083
Mr. Corleone.

216
00:22:11,187 --> 00:22:13,246
- Two seconds.
- Frank, how are you?

217
00:22:13,356 --> 00:22:15,847
Thank you very much for your
contribution to the Board's swimming pool,...

218
00:22:15,959 --> 00:22:20,191
...and we need your help on
Sam Wallace's candidacy for judgeship.

219
00:22:20,297 --> 00:22:22,527
- We always can use a good judge.
- Thank you.

220
00:22:22,632 --> 00:22:24,497
Andrew.

221
00:22:24,601 --> 00:22:28,933
Your Excellency, my Godson, Andrew Hagan
my brother Tom Hagen's eldest boy

222
00:22:29,039 --> 00:22:32,440
He's been assistant
to Bishop Breelan three years now.

223
00:22:32,542 --> 00:22:34,874
Hoping for an assignment to the Vatican.

224
00:22:34,978 --> 00:22:37,572
There's always a place in Rome
for a fine young priest.

225
00:22:37,681 --> 00:22:40,315
His mother, Theresa Hagen. Archbishop Gilday.

226
00:22:40,316 --> 00:22:42,878
Thank you.
It's an honor to meet you.

227
00:22:42,986 --> 00:22:47,446
Mr. Corleone, hi.
Grace Hamilton.

228
00:22:47,557 --> 00:22:52,395
Vincent Mancini promised that he'd tell
you about me, that maybe you'd see me.

229
00:22:52,495 --> 00:22:54,258
Vincent Mancini called about her?

230
00:22:54,364 --> 00:22:55,763
No.

231
00:22:55,865 --> 00:22:58,597
Grace, you promised me you'd stay up there.

232
00:22:58,601 --> 00:23:00,566
- I know. I know.
- Twice.

233
00:23:01,171 --> 00:23:05,005
Joey Zasa showed up.
We've got him waiting in the lobby.

234
00:23:05,108 --> 00:23:09,135
Says he wants to personally
congratulate you and show his respect.

235
00:23:09,245 --> 00:23:11,179
Do I have to see him?

236
00:23:11,281 --> 00:23:14,478
<i>He says you're his padrone
and he only wants a minute.</i>

237
00:23:18,021 --> 00:23:20,751
Hey, Vinnie.

238
00:23:20,857 --> 00:23:23,018
- Who's your favorite Aunt?
- You are.

239
00:23:26,129 --> 00:23:30,293
Today I'm going to talk to Michael
about your problem.

240
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:33,130
I wish you would have warned me, Con.
I could have worn a better suit.

