00:42:15,491 --> 00:42:17,391
$600 million.

479
00:42:22,297 --> 00:42:26,063
Don't overestimate the power of forgiveness.

480
00:42:27,703 --> 00:42:31,730
Don Corleone. This deal with Immobiliare...

481
00:42:31,840 --> 00:42:34,707
...can make you one of the richest men in the world.

482
00:42:34,810 --> 00:42:40,407
Your whole past history, and the history
of your family, will be washed away.

483
00:42:44,520 --> 00:42:46,181
600 million.

484
00:43:02,137 --> 00:43:07,171
<i>[Keinszig] The motion and a discussion
relates to the Corleone group's proposal,...</i>

485
00:43:07,242 --> 00:43:12,308
<i>...to acquire 100 million newly issued,
Class A, quoted shares...</i>

486
00:43:13,749 --> 00:43:15,683
<i>Once issued, the shares will permit...</i>

487
00:43:15,784 --> 00:43:21,484
<i>[B.J. Harrison] ...$600 million and Corleone capital
invested directly into International Immobiliare,...</i>

488
00:43:21,523 --> 00:43:25,619
<i>...an old and respected European company...</i>

489
00:43:25,727 --> 00:43:31,205
<i>...that Michael Corleone has an ambitious program
to expand this real estate holding company,...</i>

490
00:43:31,300 --> 00:43:35,029
<i>...into an international conglomerate
that could meet the challenge...</i>

491
00:43:35,037 --> 00:43:40,034
<i>...not by political ideologies, but by
Eastern techniques of efficiency,...</i>

492
00:43:40,039 --> 00:43:42,968
- ...Mr. Corleone!
- ...and focus, and unlimited...

493
00:43:43,078 --> 00:43:45,376
Mr. Corleone, excuse me.

494
00:43:45,480 --> 00:43:49,648
Isn't it true that you recently deposited
$200 million in the Vatican bank...

495
00:43:49,651 --> 00:43:52,477
...which is affiliated with International Immobiliare?

496
00:43:52,588 --> 00:43:55,686
- This is true. Why not?
- Well, wasn't there any questioning...

497
00:43:55,690 --> 00:44:00,931
...about the timing on, on this particular deposit,
or wasn't there some talk...

498
00:44:00,929 --> 00:44:03,229
- Mr. Chairman, if I may?
- ...about the, the fact that...

499
00:44:04,700 --> 00:44:09,332
The Vito Andolini Corleone Foundation,
of which Mr. Corleone's daughter Mary is chairman,...

500
00:44:09,338 --> 00:44:12,739
...has established an endowment
in the amount of $100 million.

501
00:44:12,841 --> 00:44:17,271
The money comes from his own family
and will be administered by the Vatican.

502
00:44:17,346 --> 00:44:18,836
Answer your question?

503
00:44:20,048 --> 00:44:22,546
I have always believed...

504
00:44:22,951 --> 00:44:26,785
...helping your fellow man
is profitable in every sense...

505
00:44:26,889 --> 00:44:29,255
...personally and bottom-line.

506
00:44:29,358 --> 00:44:35,352
My fellow shareholders,
if Europe and America can learn to cooperate...

507
00:44:35,530 --> 00:44:39,398
...if we can learn to pool our wealth,
share our markets...

508
00:44:39,501 --> 00:44:44,566
...we can defeat any competition anywhere in the world.

509
00:44:45,474 --> 00:44:50,652
Let me thank you for the time you have given me
here today, and I hope, that you will look favorably...

510
00:44:50,656 --> 00:44:52,604
...on my proposal. Thank you.

511
00:44:58,253 --> 00:45:01,347
Listen, let me at this microphone here!

512
00:45:01,456 --> 00:45:04,721
How can we let a criminal like that, run our company?

513
00:45:04,826 --> 00:45:07,453
He's got the map of Sicily on his face,
can't you see it?

514
00:45:07,462 --> 00:45:13,453
- Order! Order!   - He's either a Catholic
or a Mafiosi and I say how do you like them bananas?

515
00:45:13,602 --> 00:45:17,361
The Hamilton Investor's group cannot support this proposal.

516
00:45:18,774 --> 00:45:21,242
Your excellency?

517
00:45:21,343 --> 00:45:26,162
Mr. Chairman, the Vatican Bank feels,...

518
00:45:26,248 --> 00:45:30,015
...that international Immobiliare...

519
00:45:31,620 --> 00:45:35,781
...will be safe in Mr. Corleone's hands.

520
00:45:35,791 --> 00:45:41,095
Subject to audit and final ratification
which must take place in Rome,...

521
00:45:41,196 --> 00:45:44,324
...please join me in welcoming Mr. Michael Corleone.

522
00:45:54,776 --> 00:45:57,035
<i>- Dad?
- Uh huh?</i>

523
00:45:59,147 --> 00:46:02,514
Tony says that I'm a front for the foundation.

524
00:46:04,186 --> 00:46:07,849
That you're using me just to pull the strings.

525
00:46:07,956 --> 00:46:11,050
- To get the money where you want it...
- Oh come on, please.

526
00:46:11,159 --> 00:46:13,593
...to shine up your public image.

527
00:46:13,764 --> 00:46:19,698
Mary. Mary, this is real this foundation, it's real.

528
00:46:21,803 --> 00:46:24,431
I wanted Anthony to be a part of it.

529
00:46:24,539 --> 00:46:29,014
I wanted -- I thought the two of you
would be together on this. I won't interfere.

530
00:46:29,111 --> 00:46:31,679
- I'll help, only, only if you ask.
- But...

531
00:46:31,680 --> 00:46:36,352
...what is this really for?
Why are you doing this?

532
00:46:36,451 --> 00:46:39,181
Why am I doing this?

533
00:46:39,287 --> 00:46:44,515
I'm doing this for my children.
You're doing it for your children too.

534
00:46:45,260 --> 00:46:48,320
This foundation is supposed to help all people.

535
00:46:48,430 --> 00:46:50,762
Of course, that's the purpose.

536
00:46:50,866 --> 00:46:53,494
This is legitimate, Mary.

537
00:46:53,602 --> 00:46:55,802
I swear this is legitimate.

538
00:46:59,775 --> 00:47:03,074
Dad, I want this to bring me closer to you.

539
00:47:11,086 --> 00:47:15,496
I would burn in hell, to keep you safe.

540
00:47:28,904 --> 00:47:33,539
No no, no, you go in the other car,
I'll ride with Michael. Go, go, go.

541
00:47:47,989 --> 00:47:53,787
As your family's oldest friend,
I'm always chosen to bring you messages.

542
00:47:56,164 --> 00:47:58,564
Tell me, Don Altobello.

543
00:48:01,002 --> 00:48:05,095
Your old partners are grateful
for the money you've made them...

544
00:48:05,107 --> 00:48:08,372
...they, they worship you.

545
00:48:08,477 --> 00:48:11,310
But their hearts are broken...

546
00:48:11,413 --> 00:48:14,871
...because they think you abandoned them.

547
00:48:14,983 --> 00:48:18,612
They want to share your deal on Immobiliare.

548
00:48:19,621 --> 00:48:24,151
To be a family again.
It can purify their money.

549
00:48:26,528 --> 00:48:27,927
This I cannot do.

550
00:48:31,032 --> 00:48:34,092
Immobiliare must be legitimate.

551
00:48:35,937 --> 00:48:40,571
I know. But they're unhappy.

552
00:48:43,078 --> 00:48:44,841
And you?

553
00:48:44,946 --> 00:48:48,844
I ask nothing for myself.

554
00:48:48,917 --> 00:48:51,078
Only peace in my old age.

555
00:48:51,186 --> 00:48:54,314
But I - I must please the world around me.

556
00:48:56,458 --> 00:49:00,952
Michael, your father was a reasonable man.

557
00:49:01,062 --> 00:49:02,962
Learn from him.

558
00:49:04,733 --> 00:49:08,635
I learned many things from my father.

559
00:49:13,708 --> 00:49:16,006
Call a meeting, my friend.

560
00:49:16,111 --> 00:49:20,172
So there are no debts, or grudges.

561
00:49:20,282 --> 00:49:23,745
We will make the peace. You and I.

562
00:50:03,058 --> 00:50:05,117
They just had a press conference.

563
00:50:05,227 --> 00:50:10,188
They said the Pope's condition was grave.
Gravisimo, they said.

564
00:50:46,167 --> 00:50:50,066
Please. Our group represents...

565
00:50:50,171 --> 00:50:56,169
...a consortium of Catholic businessmen,
against the Corleone control.

566
00:50:56,278 --> 00:51:01,679
The Vatican has cast its vote.
The Corleone group already controls the board.

567
00:51:01,783 --> 00:51:05,785
According to the lateran treaty,
the Vatican support must be ratified...

568
00:51:05,787 --> 00:51:09,518
...here in Rome by the Pope.

569
00:51:13,061 --> 00:51:16,360
The Pope is gravely ill.

570
00:51:17,599 --> 00:51:22,390
Until he recovers, I am powerless.

571
00:51:22,437 --> 00:51:24,667
What if he dies?

572
00:51:24,773 --> 00:51:29,565
Then, as you Americans say, all bets are off.

573
00:51:29,644 --> 00:51:35,548
Gentlemen please, this is a brief delay.

574
00:51:35,650 --> 00:51:37,140
Nothing more.

575
00:51:41,656 --> 00:51:45,148
Your excellency, gentlemen...

576
00:51:45,260 --> 00:51:51,199
...I advise, you join us in our prayers
for the Holy Father’s recovery.

577
00:51:52,100 --> 00:51:53,795
Now we had an agreement!

578
00:51:55,070 --> 00:51:58,972
And this meeting was to be merely,
a formality, that's all it was.

579
00:51:59,074 --> 00:52:02,510
- Please sit down.
- I'd rather stand. Could someone just give me an answer?

580
00:52:02,610 --> 00:52:08,353
- We have put ourselves on the line...
- The Immobiliare has its roots in the European tradition.

581
00:52:08,450 --> 00:52:09,917
Please try to understand.

582
00:52:10,018 --> 00:52:14,088
I understand. Your tactics are despicable.

583
00:52:14,189 --> 00:52:17,755
Well, that's quite an indictment,
coming from a Corleone.

584
00:52:17,759 --> 00:52:22,792
Gentlemen - gentlemen!
Remember, you are in the Vatican, please.

585
00:52:25,633 --> 00:52:28,033
What is it that you want?

586
00:52:28,136 --> 00:52:32,198
Yes -- you will take control.

587
00:52:32,240 --> 00:52:36,199
We'll gladly put you at the helm of our little fleet.

588
00:52:36,311 --> 00:52:40,543
But our ships, must all sail in the same direction.

589
00:52:41,783 --> 00:52:47,516
Otherwise, who can say how long,
your stay with us will last?

590
00:52:49,657 --> 00:52:53,766
It's not personal, it's only business.

591
00:52:53,862 --> 00:52:56,292
You should know, Godfather.

592
00:52:59,534 --> 00:53:05,102
Very well. You want to do business with me.

593
00:53:05,206 --> 00:53:10,399
I will, do business, with you.
Vipers, all of them.

594
00:53:16,484 --> 00:53:19,419
- We're back with the Borgias.
- Uncle Michael.

595
00:53:19,521 --> 00:53:21,148
Andrew.

596
00:53:21,256 --> 00:53:24,316
I heard you were here.
It's so nice to see you.

597
00:53:24,426 --> 00:53:27,190
- Vincent.
- How are you, Andrew? - You look so nice.

598
00:53:27,295 --> 00:53:30,787
Listen, what is this with the Borgias?
Those days are over Uncle Michael...

599
00:53:36,070 --> 00:53:39,471
- Recognize it?
- Yeah.

600
00:53:39,574 --> 00:53:41,701
Genco Olive Oil.

601
00:53:41,810 --> 00:53:46,485
That's where our Grandfather got his start.
Started as a delivery boy, made three bucks a week.

602
00:53:46,481 --> 00:53:48,481
Three years later, he owned the company.

603
00:53:48,583 --> 00:53:51,677
- Only in America.
- That's it.

604
00:53:51,786 --> 00:53:56,989
Hey Vincenzo, where have you been hiding?
You deserted us, and we need your help so badly.

605
00:53:56,991 --> 00:53:58,653
Well now I'm back, what can I do for you?

606
00:53:58,659 --> 00:54:01,219
Get rid of Joe Zasa.
He sells drugs to children.

607
00:54:01,329 --> 00:54:04,189
Listen, when I was a young girl it was different.
Now I'm an old woman...

608
00:54:04,198 --> 00:54:05,961
...I'm afraid to walk the streets at night, you know?

609
00:54:05,967 --> 00:54:08,233
Where are they supposed to be at?

610
00:54:08,336 --> 00:54:10,668
<i>- Lou, what's going on?
- He's going pazzo.</i>

611
00:54:10,772 --> 00:54:12,897
- We're late.
- Don't tell me that garbage.

612
00:54:12,907 --> 00:54:15,967
- Have I ever let you down?
- I trust you.

613
00:54:16,077 --> 00:54:18,511
- Don't worry about it.
- Thank you very much.

614
00:54:18,613 --> 00:54:20,444
- Bye bye.
- Enjoy yourself.

615
00:54:26,855 --> 00:54:31,688
- What was that?
- The neighborhood's in trouble.

616
00:54:31,726 --> 00:54:34,786
- You keep your eye out for them?
- That's right.

617
00:54:34,896 --> 00:54:37,694
- And for me?
- From now on.

618
00:54:37,799 --> 00:54:40,029
I missed you all this time.

619
00:54:40,134 --> 00:54:42,534
I missed you, too, cousin.

620
00:54:42,637 --> 00:54:45,538
I missed growing up with all my cousins.

621
00:54:45,640 --> 00:54:48,074
I didn't even know you and I missed you.

622
00:54:48,176 --> 00:54:53,345
Do you remember stories about our fathers,
the old days?

623
00:54:53,347 --> 00:54:55,547
Yeah. What do you want to know?

624
00:54:58,019 --> 00:54:59,577
What was Sonny like?

625
00:55:02,190 --> 00:55:04,784
He was the Prince of the city.

626
00:55:04,893 --> 00:55:08,727
Yeah -- he died before I was born but I
heard a million stories about him, he was a legend.

627
00:55:10,498 --> 00:55:12,591
What about my father?

628
00:55:12,700 --> 00:55:18,268
A great man, your father.
He's a hero, he saved the family.

629
00:55:19,541 --> 00:55:21,441
- Vincent.
- What?

630
00:55:21,543 --> 00:55:24,273
Did he kill his own brother?

631
00:55:28,274 --> 00:55:29,274
No.

632
00:55:32,120 --> 00:55:34,782
So those are all lies?

633
00:55:38,126 --> 00:55:41,826
Just stories, sweetheart. Okay?

634
00:55:45,269 --> 00:55:49,863
Okay. I believe you.

635
00:55:51,372 --> 00:55:55,308
- I'm glad you're around.
- I'm glad you're here too.

636
00:56:18,032 --> 00:56:21,365
I'd like to take Joey Zasa up
for a ride in this and drop him.

637
00:56:21,469 --> 00:56:24,370
Joey Zasa is nothing.

638
00:56:24,472 --> 00:56:26,940
He's a small-time enforcer.

639
00:56:27,041 --> 00:56:29,839
He bluffs, threats, but nothing.

640
00:56:29,944 --> 00:56:32,669
We'll be able to see him coming, a mile away.

641
00:56:33,414 --> 00:56:35,575
- We should kill him before he kills...
- No.

642
00:56:38,820 --> 00:56:43,888
Never hate your enemies. It affects your judgment.

643
00:56:58,773 --> 00:57:02,265
Good evening.
Nice to see you again, Mr. Corleone.

644
00:57:22,563 --> 00:57:25,498
Okay, girls, let's go.
Come on, girls.

645
00:57:42,717 --> 00:57:47,086
We entrusted you to manage our money in the casinos.

646
00:57:47,188 --> 00:57:53,093
It's not even 20 years. You sold the casinos,
and you made fortunes for all of us.

647
00:57:53,194 --> 00:57:55,094
Bravo, Don Corleone!

648
00:57:57,565 --> 00:57:58,691
Thank you.

649
00:57:59,901 --> 00:58:03,234
Friends, I have come here...

650
00:58:03,337 --> 00:58:07,000
...because our business together is done.

651
00:58:08,409 --> 00:58:12,140
We have prospered, and now it is time for us...

652
00:58:12,246 --> 00:58:15,543
...to dissolve the business relationship between us.

653
00:58:17,251 --> 00:58:22,646
That's it. But I do have a little surprise. Al?

654
00:58:25,326 --> 00:58:28,124
Your shares in the casino.

655
00:58:28,229 --> 00:58:32,629
I thought I'd cut through all the red tape
so you can get your money right away.

656
00:58:38,673 --> 00:58:42,973
- $50 million!
- Not everybody gets the same.

657
00:58:43,077 --> 00:58:47,011
- It depends how much you invested, and how long for.
- nothing for you.

658
00:58:47,115 --> 00:58:50,084
Michael, this is really generous!

659
00:58:50,184 --> 00:58:52,243
Oh, wonderful.

660
00:58:55,356 --> 00:58:59,824
- Hey, Perisi, how much did you invest?
- I don't remember.

661
00:58:59,827 --> 00:59:02,454
Michael, you're blessed.

662
00:59:07,535 --> 00:59:12,844
My family has done much of the hard work;
taken many risks.

663
00:59:14,475 --> 00:59:17,735
All to make money, for the rest of the families.

664
00:59:19,947 --> 00:59:22,780
You all know Joey Zasa.

665
00:59:22,884 --> 00:59:25,284
He is, I admit, an important man.

666
00:59:26,420 --> 00:59:30,618
<i>His picture is on the cover
of the New York Times magazine.</i>

667
00:59:30,725 --> 00:59:33,319
<i>He gets the Esquire magazine award,...</i>

668
00:59:33,427 --> 00:59:35,952
...for the best-dressed gangster.

669
00:59:36,063 --> 00:59:37,963
The newspapers praise him...

670
00:59:38,065 --> 00:59:42,663
...because, he hires Blacks into his family,
which shows he has a good heart.

671
00:59:44,906 --> 00:59:47,431
He is famous.

672
00:59:47,542 --> 00:59:51,342
Who knows?
Maybe one day...

673
00:59:51,445 --> 00:59:54,109
...he will make all of you popular.

674
00:59:55,316 --> 00:59:56,715
It's true.

675
00:59:56,818 --> 01:00:02,454
<i>I make more of a bella figura.
That is my nature.</i>

676
01:00:02,456 --> 01:00:07,589
But I also want to make a move
into legitimate enterprises.

677
01:00:07,595 --> 01:00:10,359
I'd like to get a little pin from the Pope.

678
01:00:10,464 --> 01:00:15,902
Sure, I take the Blacks and the Spanish into my family...

679
01:00:16,003 --> 01:00:19,504
...because that's America.

680
01:00:19,507 --> 01:00:24,274
And you guarantee that they don't
deal drugs in those neighborhoods.

681
01:00:25,379 --> 01:00:30,578
I don't guarantee that.
I guarantee I'll kill anybody who does.

682
01:00:34,689 --> 01:00:37,453
Let me talk to him, let me talk to him.

683
01:00:37,558 --> 01:00:40,088
Who can refuse Don Altobello?

684
01:00:43,130 --> 01:00:47,430
No! I say to all of you,
I have been treated this day...

685
01:00:47,535 --> 01:00:49,935
...with no respect.

686
01:00:50,037 --> 01:00:55,373
I've earned you all money.
I've made you rich, and I asked for little.

687
01:00:55,476 --> 01:00:59,378
Good. You will not give?
I'll take.

688
01:01:00,648 --> 01:01:03,308
As for Don Corleone...

689
01:01:03,317 --> 01:01:07,480
...well, he makes it very clear to me today...

690
01:01:07,488 --> 01:01:10,285
...that he is my enemy.

691
01:01:13,294 --> 01:01:15,694
You must choose between us.

692
01:01:24,272 --> 01:01:28,831
We can reason together - no - Michael,

693
01:01:28,841 --> 01:01:33,505
Michael - please, let's agreed, huh?

694
01:01:33,614 --> 01:01:35,514
He doesn't know what he's...

695
01:01:41,991 --> 01:01:45,991
...Uh, Michael, Michael. The news is everywhere.

696
01:01:46,093 --> 01:01:49,995
Everyone is saying that, that you control Immobiliare.

697
01:01:50,097 --> 01:01:55,698
Immobiliare already is laundering money in Peru,
in Nassau, we know that.

698
01:01:55,703 --> 01:01:59,300
Listen to me, Michael.
We've been friends for 40 years.

699
01:01:59,407 --> 01:02:01,270
We should wet our beaks a little.

700
01:02:01,275 --> 01:02:04,640
- We want to do business with you, Michael.
- That's right.

701
01:02:04,645 --> 01:02:08,483
- We've been together for many.
- We can wash our money clean with holy water.

702
01:02:13,821 --> 01:02:15,652
What the hell is that?

703
01:02:15,756 --> 01:02:18,519
- It's a hit. Let's go. Follow me.
- Let's get outta here!

704
01:02:38,312 --> 01:02:41,213
- My coat! It's my lucky coat!
- Forget your coat.

705
01:02:42,316 --> 01:02:44,147
It's my lucky coat!

706
01:02:50,324 --> 01:02:51,923
Stay right behind me!

707
01:03:07,308 --> 01:03:09,942
- Fuck!
- Mikey, this way!

708
01:03:19,520 --> 01:03:21,886
Zasa! You son of a bitch!

709
01:03:41,642 --> 01:03:43,701
Come on, we're outta here.

710
01:04:16,744 --> 01:04:19,143
- You did good, Vincent.
- Grazie.

711
01:04:19,580 --> 01:04:22,674
The old Dons were pretty much wiped out.

712
01:04:22,783 --> 01:04:27,984
