- Yes, it was then.

945
01:32:09,244 --> 01:32:11,235
I worry about you now.

946
01:32:11,244 --> 01:32:16,475
Oh Mary. Mary you're such a warm-hearted girl,
you always were.

947
01:32:16,484 --> 01:32:20,315
- I love my family.
- Even your cousin Vincent?

948
01:32:24,126 --> 01:32:26,089
I really love him.

949
01:32:27,562 --> 01:32:31,794
- He's your first cousin.
- Then I love him first.

950
01:32:31,900 --> 01:32:34,630
Mary, you can't see him.

951
01:32:34,736 --> 01:32:38,103
Just don't see him anymore.

952
01:32:38,206 --> 01:32:42,040
He's right.
It's too dangerous.

953
01:32:44,412 --> 01:32:47,945
Mary, listen to me.
You can't see him anymore.

954
01:32:47,949 --> 01:32:49,878
- Not in that fashion.
- No.

955
01:32:51,619 --> 01:32:54,912
- Please, promise me.
- No!

956
01:32:54,990 --> 01:32:57,388
- Obey me on this Mary!
- No, Dad!

957
01:33:02,731 --> 01:33:07,065
Mary's smart, Dad.
She'll understand eventually.

958
01:33:43,839 --> 01:33:47,036
- You wanted to see me?
- Yeah.

959
01:33:47,142 --> 01:33:49,644
- I want you to do something for me.
- Okay.

960
01:33:49,645 --> 01:33:51,545
It's dangerous.

961
01:33:52,647 --> 01:33:56,483
Good, I'm in.
What do you need?

962
01:33:56,484 --> 01:34:02,191
I want you to sell your soul to Don Altobello to betray me.

963
01:34:05,527 --> 01:34:08,491
He'd never believe me.
Here.

964
01:34:08,496 --> 01:34:10,826
- That depends.
- Sit down.

965
01:34:13,869 --> 01:34:15,769
I have an idea.

966
01:34:17,038 --> 01:34:20,940
See if you can learn
how high Altobello is connected.

967
01:34:24,713 --> 01:34:26,613
Arrange a meeting.

968
01:34:29,150 --> 01:34:34,281
You say how devoted you are to me.
Tell him your problems.

969
01:34:34,389 --> 01:34:38,090
- You ask for his help.
- What problems?

970
01:34:39,461 --> 01:34:41,661
That you want to run away with my daughter.

971
01:34:42,998 --> 01:34:47,401
Only you know that if you do,
I will become your enemy.

972
01:34:52,140 --> 01:34:54,370
You know I would never do that, Uncle Mike.

973
01:34:54,476 --> 01:34:55,534
I know.

974
01:34:56,811 --> 01:35:01,846
<i>You ask Altobello to speak to me.
To further the marriage.</i>

975
01:35:01,917 --> 01:35:04,215
But you're cousins, after all.

976
01:35:04,319 --> 01:35:07,755
Michael was always a little old-fashioned.

977
01:35:08,056 --> 01:35:13,194
<i>Explain to him how, you can never be part of my,
legitimate world. That you want your own family.</i>

978
01:35:13,261 --> 01:35:17,163
I could straighten out what Joey Zasa left behind.

979
01:35:18,900 --> 01:35:21,300
If you could use your friendship to persuade him.

980
01:35:22,837 --> 01:35:25,237
I would be indebted to you forever.

981
01:35:27,709 --> 01:35:31,611
Corleone, knows the value of such a friend.

982
01:35:33,081 --> 01:35:35,481
So then you would work for me?

983
01:35:44,125 --> 01:35:45,786
<i>Remember...</i>

984
01:35:45,894 --> 01:35:50,831
...if he hints that he wants you to betray me, get insulted.

985
01:35:50,932 --> 01:35:52,866
Because that's his trap.

986
01:36:00,508 --> 01:36:03,409
You're not telling me the whole truth, Vincenzo.

987
01:36:06,781 --> 01:36:10,512
Isn't it true, with Michael gone...

988
01:36:10,618 --> 01:36:13,018
...the girl controls everything?

989
01:36:16,524 --> 01:36:18,617
You leave the girl out of this.

990
01:36:18,727 --> 01:36:22,128
Of course, you love her, and she loves you.

991
01:36:43,251 --> 01:36:45,651
I guessed it Vincenzo, huh?

992
01:36:47,288 --> 01:36:50,689
You're a wise man, Don Altobello.

993
01:36:50,792 --> 01:36:53,420
I'm going to be learning a lot from you.

994
01:36:53,528 --> 01:36:56,458
The richest man is the one
with the most powerful friends.

995
01:36:59,033 --> 01:37:02,396
It's my duty to make the introductions.

996
01:37:09,177 --> 01:37:11,077
Don Lucchesi.

997
01:37:13,915 --> 01:37:19,743
Don Altobello tells me you have a good character,
strong, a man of respect.

998
01:37:19,821 --> 01:37:23,621
This is the hero who put Joey Zasa in his grave.

999
01:37:23,725 --> 01:37:28,025
If we'd have known of his existence,
we would never have backed Joey.

1000
01:37:28,129 --> 01:37:33,469
No one wants another Joe.
Let me be your friend.

1001
01:37:35,003 --> 01:37:37,938
Even the strongest man needs friends.

1002
01:37:38,039 --> 01:37:43,239
I'm flattered.
But you're a man of finance and politics, Don Lucchesi,...

1003
01:37:43,244 --> 01:37:45,144
...these are things I don't understand.

1004
01:37:46,914 --> 01:37:48,142
You understand guns.

1005
01:37:49,083 --> 01:37:51,108
Finance is a gun.

1006
01:37:51,219 --> 01:37:55,815
Politics is knowing when to pull the trigger.

1007
01:38:00,361 --> 01:38:01,589
How can I help?

1008
01:38:07,268 --> 01:38:12,872
Blessed is the peacemaker,
for he can be can be called a child of God.

1009
01:38:48,877 --> 01:38:52,438
I trusted this business arrangement
with the Archbishop.

1010
01:38:52,547 --> 01:38:57,644
I trusted him.
I was sure his honesty was beyond a doubt.

1011
01:38:57,652 --> 01:39:02,954
But, as you see, I'm now the victim of a swindle.

1012
01:39:03,058 --> 01:39:04,958
They're stalling me.

1013
01:39:05,060 --> 01:39:09,019
<i>Vast moneys have gone to the pezzonovante
in high political places...</i>

1014
01:39:09,130 --> 01:39:11,860
...and the Vatican bank is the guarantor.

1015
01:39:11,966 --> 01:39:17,233
If uh, what you say is true, there will be a great scandal.

1016
01:39:19,207 --> 01:39:24,338
Look at this stone. It has been lying
in the water for a very long time,...

1017
01:39:24,446 --> 01:39:28,348
...but the water has not penetrated it.

1018
01:39:32,387 --> 01:39:36,289
Look. Perfectly dry.

1019
01:39:37,525 --> 01:39:39,891
The same thing has happened to men in Europe.

1020
01:39:39,994 --> 01:39:44,897
For centuries, they have been
surrounded by Christianity,...

1021
01:39:44,999 --> 01:39:47,524
...but Christ has not penetrated.

1022
01:39:47,635 --> 01:39:51,036
Christ doesn't breathe within them.

1023
01:39:55,076 --> 01:39:57,203
- What's happening?
- Is it possible...

1024
01:39:57,312 --> 01:40:00,247
...that you could get me something sweet?

1025
01:40:00,348 --> 01:40:02,748
Orange juice, anything, a candy.

1026
01:40:06,321 --> 01:40:08,380
I have a little trouble with diabetes.

1027
01:40:12,360 --> 01:40:14,260
Blood sugar levels must be low.

1028
01:40:15,396 --> 01:40:17,296
I understand.

1029
01:40:39,787 --> 01:40:43,450
When I'm under stress, sometimes this happens.

1030
01:40:43,558 --> 01:40:45,458
I understand.

1031
01:40:47,295 --> 01:40:50,896
I come to you, on such a delicate matter...

1032
01:40:53,835 --> 01:40:56,804
...accusations against your Archbishop.

1033
01:40:56,905 --> 01:40:58,964
It was difficult for me.

1034
01:41:00,208 --> 01:41:06,153
The mind suffers and the body, cries out.

1035
01:41:10,985 --> 01:41:13,044
That's true.

1036
01:41:14,522 --> 01:41:18,856
Would you like, to make your confession?

1037
01:41:25,500 --> 01:41:29,059
Your Eminence, I'm uh - I'm uh...

1038
01:41:31,372 --> 01:41:37,011
...it's been so long, I wouldn't -
I wouldn't - I wouldn't know where to uh,...

1039
01:41:38,346 --> 01:41:40,246
...it's been 30 years.

1040
01:41:41,383 --> 01:41:44,874
I'd - I'd - I'd use up too much of your time, I think.

1041
01:41:44,986 --> 01:41:48,280
I always have time to save souls.

1042
01:41:49,490 --> 01:41:52,591
Well, I'm -- I'm beyond redemption.

1043
01:42:03,705 --> 01:42:08,765
I hear the confessions of my young priests here.

1044
01:42:08,776 --> 01:42:12,710
Sometimes the desire to confess is overwhelming...

1045
01:42:12,714 --> 01:42:15,114
...and we must seize the moment.

1046
01:42:20,121 --> 01:42:24,749
What is the point of confessing if I don't repent?

1047
01:42:26,361 --> 01:42:29,660
I hear you are a practical man.

1048
01:42:29,764 --> 01:42:33,024
What have you got to lose, huh?

1049
01:42:43,745 --> 01:42:44,975
Go on.

1050
01:42:51,919 --> 01:42:56,368
I uh, betrayed my wife.

1051
01:42:57,992 --> 01:42:59,892
Go on, my son.

1052
01:43:05,300 --> 01:43:07,200
I betrayed myself.

1053
01:43:10,071 --> 01:43:11,971
I killed men.

1054
01:43:15,710 --> 01:43:18,110
And I ordered men to be killed.

1055
01:43:19,747 --> 01:43:21,647
Go on, my son, go on.

1056
01:43:26,789 --> 01:43:29,017
Nah, it's useless.

1057
01:43:31,092 --> 01:43:32,992
Go on, my son.

1058
01:43:34,095 --> 01:43:35,995
I killed...

1059
01:43:40,735 --> 01:43:44,398
...I ordered the death of my brother.

1060
01:43:44,505 --> 01:43:46,405
He injured me.

1061
01:43:47,809 --> 01:43:50,403
I killed my mother's son.

1062
01:43:51,779 --> 01:43:53,872
I killed my father's son.

1063
01:44:04,592 --> 01:44:09,397
Your sins are terrible, and it is just that you suffer.

1064
01:44:10,565 --> 01:44:16,195
Your life, could be redeemed,
but I know that you don't believe that.

1065
01:44:16,204 --> 01:44:18,104
You will not change.

1066
01:45:10,305 --> 01:45:11,505
Connie,...

1067
01:45:13,694 --> 01:45:17,896
...all my life I, kept trying to go up in society,...

1068
01:45:18,833 --> 01:45:22,334
...where everything higher up was legal, straight.

1069
01:45:23,704 --> 01:45:26,864
But the higher I go, the crookeder it becomes.

1070
01:45:30,044 --> 01:45:32,103
How in the hell does it end?

1071
01:45:41,189 --> 01:45:44,190
Killing each other for centuries here.

1072
01:45:45,927 --> 01:45:50,296
For money, for pride, for family.

1073
01:45:53,367 --> 01:45:57,369
<i>To keep from becoming the slaves
of the rich pezzonovante.</i>

1074
01:46:04,412 --> 01:46:10,371
I made confession, Connie.
I confessed my sins.

1075
01:46:11,319 --> 01:46:17,390
Why Michael, that's not like you.
You don't have to confess your sins to a stranger.

1076
01:46:17,391 --> 01:46:18,824
It was the man.

1077
01:46:20,228 --> 01:46:24,375
A good man. A true priest.

1078
01:46:28,069 --> 01:46:29,969
He can change things.

1079
01:46:32,270 --> 01:46:33,470
Michael,...

1080
01:46:35,343 --> 01:46:41,082
...you know, sometimes I think of poor Fredo, drowned.

1081
01:46:42,149 --> 01:46:44,049
It was God's will.

1082
01:46:45,920 --> 01:46:48,320
It was a terrible accident.

1083
01:46:49,423 --> 01:46:51,323
But it's finished.

1084
01:46:56,731 --> 01:46:58,631
Michael, I love you.

1085
01:47:01,002 --> 01:47:02,902
I'll always help you.

1086
01:47:12,713 --> 01:47:14,613
It's okay.

1087
01:49:54,742 --> 01:49:57,233
- Welcome.
- Oh, Connie! How are you?

1088
01:49:57,344 --> 01:50:00,936
- Mary, I missed you.
- I've missed you too.

1089
01:50:00,948 --> 01:50:02,848
- Well, hello Michael.
- Hello Kay.

1090
01:50:02,950 --> 01:50:08,519
- Mom, look at this.
- What, let me see - oh! My - wow!

1091
01:50:08,522 --> 01:50:10,949
You know it's too bad that Douglas couldn't be with us.

1092
01:50:10,958 --> 01:50:14,555
No, no, I know. He wanted to come very much,
but he had a very important trial.

1093
01:50:14,562 --> 01:50:17,690
- I know he wanted to come.
- I know.

1094
01:50:17,798 --> 01:50:19,698
- The car is...
- Okay.

1095
01:50:21,736 --> 01:50:25,797
Well, your son's an artist, huh?

1096
01:50:25,906 --> 01:50:29,599
- Oh, yes, thanks to you.
- Oh, what for?

1097
01:50:30,678 --> 01:50:34,942
- For making me let him go.
- Oh, well.

1098
01:50:35,049 --> 01:50:38,880
After all these years,
here I am in Sicily for the first time.

1099
01:50:38,886 --> 01:50:41,586
- I want to get a picture of you together.
- Oh, Okay.

1100
01:50:43,958 --> 01:50:45,858
Hey, Dad, smile.

1101
01:50:49,830 --> 01:50:53,261
I see you still have Al Neri.
Why?

1102
01:50:54,502 --> 01:50:58,834
Well, I need him.
He helps me get in and out of the car.

1103
01:50:58,839 --> 01:51:01,137
Carry my briefcase.

1104
01:51:01,242 --> 01:51:03,938
You're still a liar, Michael.

1105
01:51:04,044 --> 01:51:07,502
Let me show you Sicily. The real Sicily.

1106
01:51:07,615 --> 01:51:10,513
Maybe you'll understand
the family history a little better.

1107
01:51:10,518 --> 01:51:12,918
Oh I think I understand it well enough.

1108
01:52:04,939 --> 01:52:08,440
Anthony, I have something you made for me...

1109
01:52:09,543 --> 01:52:11,443
...a very long time ago.

1110
01:52:12,613 --> 01:52:15,741
- It may bring you luck.
- Thanks.

1111
01:52:19,486 --> 01:52:21,044
You saved it, huh?

1112
01:52:21,155 --> 01:52:23,646
- Remember?
- I remember.

1113
01:52:26,193 --> 01:52:28,093
Thank you Dad.

1114
01:52:30,364 --> 01:52:34,273
- I'm proud of you.
- Thank you.

1115
01:52:50,451 --> 01:52:53,179
- Are they as good as they look?
- They're better.

1116
01:52:53,187 --> 01:52:58,122
They're the best.
As long as they're around, Uncle Michael is safe.

1117
01:52:58,158 --> 01:52:59,923
- Bye.
- Bye.

1118
01:53:02,630 --> 01:53:05,098
- Tell your father I'll be back for dinner.
- Okay.

1119
01:53:06,367 --> 01:53:09,129
- Have fun.
- And tell Tony to be sure to wait for me.

1120
01:53:09,136 --> 01:53:11,764
Okay, I will.

1121
01:53:11,872 --> 01:53:14,270
- Bye, mom!
- Buon giorno, Signora.

1122
01:53:14,275 --> 01:53:16,505
At your service.

1123
01:53:20,114 --> 01:53:23,515
If I see dad, I'll tell him you left.

1124
01:53:28,722 --> 01:53:32,758
You're the only one left in this family
with my father's strength.

1125
01:53:34,895 --> 01:53:39,591
If anything happens to Michael,
I want you to strike back.

1126
01:53:41,969 --> 01:53:43,527
I'll have everything ready.

1127
01:53:47,108 --> 01:53:49,008
You swear?

1128
01:53:56,317 --> 01:53:58,376
I swear to you.

1129
01:54:28,582 --> 01:54:30,482
Here it is.

1130
01:54:31,885 --> 01:54:33,944
The house where my father was born.

1131
01:54:35,589 --> 01:54:41,292
This is where they came, to take him when he was a boy.
To kill him.

1132
01:54:44,298 --> 01:54:47,699
Wait, listen to that.

1133
01:55:07,855 --> 01:55:10,013
You know, Mary's in love.

1134
01:55:11,225 --> 01:55:13,550
Yes, I know.

1135
01:55:14,161 --> 01:55:19,392
With a handsome young Italian man
with dark eyes.

1136
01:55:19,400 --> 01:55:21,300
I won't allow it.

1137
01:55:24,104 --> 01:55:28,001
It's wrong.
It's wrong, and it's dangerous.

1138
01:56:00,140 --> 01:56:01,801
Honor, huh?

1139
01:56:21,061 --> 01:56:24,330
You know, I remember the time
that you came to my parent's house.

1140
01:56:24,331 --> 01:56:27,730
And you took me into that room.
And you told me about the family business...

1141
01:56:27,734 --> 01:56:33,331
...and how you were never going to have
anything to do with it. You sounded like Tony.

1142
01:56:33,974 --> 01:56:35,874
I was a lot like Tony.

1143
01:56:43,484 --> 01:56:46,453
- I can barely see. Kay.
- What?

1144
01:56:46,553 --> 01:56:49,215
- You mind driving?
- No. What's wrong?

1145
01:56:49,323 --> 01:56:53,052
My eyes... sometimes
they're all right, and then...

1146
01:56:53,060 --> 01:56:56,288
- Ssure.
- Listen, I have to see Don Tommasino.

1147
01:56:58,265 --> 01:57:00,028
Oh! Oh, my God!

1148
01:57:00,134 --> 01:57:06,233
- Well there's no bodyguards today.
- I really snuck away.

1149
01:57:54,834 --> 01:57:59,234
- Calo, how are you?
- Hi. Nice to see you.

1150
01:57:59,293 --> 01:58:01,256
- How are you?
- Bene. - Hi.

1151
01:58:01,261 --> 01:58:03,161
- Kay, this is Calo, my old friend.
- How do you do?

1152
01:58:03,163 --> 01:58:05,063
One of my bodyguards in the old days.

1153
01:58:10,470 --> 01:58:11,969
- We can wait here.
- You want drink?

1154
01:58:11,972 --> 01:58:14,373
- Yes. Shall we go in?
- Sure.

1155
01:58:17,945 --> 01:58:21,345
I spent a lot of time in this room...

1156
01:58:22,683 --> 01:58:24,412
...thinking of you.

1157
01:58:27,554 --> 01:58:30,114
And then you got married.

1158
01:58:33,293 --> 01:58:34,851
I still thought of you.

1159
01:58:35,629 --> 01:58:37,529
What's in that room?

1160
01:58:41,335 --> 01:58:45,735
You know this is dangerous for you, Michael.
This is Sicily.

1161
01:58:47,975 --> 01:58:50,375
- I love this country.
- Why?

1162
01:58:53,080 --> 01:58:59,077
Well, all through history,
terrible things have happened to these people.

1163
01:58:59,986 --> 01:59:01,784
Terrible injustices.

1164
01:59:02,889 --> 01:59:08,222
But they still expect good
rather than bad will happen to them.

1165
01:59:08,228 --> 01:59:10,628
Sort of like me and you, huh?

1166
01:59:14,701 --> 01:59:18,068
- How so?
- Well I'm still here, right?

1167
01:59:18,171 --> 01:59:19,661
We do have a bad history.

1168
01:59:20,607 --> 01:59:24,143
- But I'm still here.
- Oh Yes, you are, but with dread.

1169
01:59:28,949 --> 01:59:30,812
Give me the order. Come on.

1170
01:59:30,817 --> 01:59:34,047
What is that supposed to do,
is that supposed to make me not dread you?

1171
01:59:36,623 --> 01:59:39,223
We're in Sicily. It's opera.

1172
01:59:41,328 --> 01:59:42,727
Okay.

1173
01:59:45,465 --> 01:59:47,524
What do we do now?

1174
01:59:50,337 --> 01:59:54,596
Be reasonable. Let's try not to hurt each other.

1175
02:00:01,782 --> 02:00:03,682
I want you to forgive me.

1176
02:00:06,453 --> 02:00:10,181
- For what?
- Everything.

1177
02:00:14,201 --> 02:00:20,090
- Like God, huh?
- Oh, I - I need something a little closer.

1178
02:00:22,769 --> 02:00:25,736
You couldn't understand back in those days...

1179
02:00:27,507 --> 02:00:32,541
I love my father.
I swore I would never be, a man like him...

1180
02:00:32,546 --> 02:00:37,147
...but I loved him.
And he was in danger; what could I do?

1181
02:00:37,150 --> 02:00:40,415
And then later you were in danger.

1182
02:00:40,520 --> 02:00:45,057
Our children were in danger.
What could I do?

1183
02:00:45,058 --> 02:00:51,150
You were all that I loved, valued, most in the world.

1184
02:00:52,165 --> 02:00:54,825
And now I'm losing you.
I lost you anyway.

1185
02:00:55,936 --> 02:01:01,176
You're gone, and it was all for nothing.

1186
02:01:01,274 --> 02:01:02,673
So...

1187
02:01:06,513 --> 02:01:11,773
...you have to understand,
I had a whole different destiny planned.

1188
02:01:15,055 --> 02:01:17,450
All right, I'll stop.

1189
02:01:27,667 --> 02:01:31,464
I really don't know what you want from me,
Michael - I really don't know.

1190
02:01:31,471 --> 02:01:36,702
- I mean...
- I'm not the man that you think I am?

1191
02:01:38,145 --> 02:01:42,013
- I don't know.
- I love you, Kay.

1192
02:01:43,216 --> 02:01:46,185
Don't dread me anymore.

1193
02:01:51,124 --> 02:01:55,864
You know, every night here in Sicily.

1194
02:01:57,097 --> 02:02:02,592
I dream, about my wife and my children.

1195
02:02:05,572 --> 02:02:08,206
And how I lost them.

1196
02:02:09,876 --> 02:02:15,871
I guess, if it's any consolation,
I want you to know that...

1197
02:02:18,952 --> 02:02:24,051
...that -- I always loved you, Michael.

1198
02:02:25,358 --> 02:02:31,351
And, you know...
I always - I always will.

1199
02:05:03,617 --> 02:05:08,091
<i>Frederik Keinszig,
known for a decade as "God's banker,"...</i>

1200
02:05:08,098 --> 02:05:12,132
<i>...has been reported missing.
He was last seen three days ago,...</i>

1201
02:05:12,135 --> 02:05:17,494
<i>...leaving the Rome offices of the Vatican
owned corporation International Immobiliare.</i>

1202
02:05:17,497 --> 02:05:21,762
<i>Also missing was a large sum of money,
and several documents.</i>

1203
02:05:21,768 --> 02:05:24,468
Come on, Keinszig, you fool.

1204
02:05:28,174 --> 02:05:33,204
<i>Mr. Keinszig's absence casts further
suspicion on the dealings of the Vatican bank.</i>

1205
02:05:33,213 --> 02:05:36,146
<i>For several years, the bank
and its subsidiary companies...</i>

1206
02:05:36,149 --> 02:05:40,709
<i>...have been the object of allegations
of disreputable business practices.</i>

1207
02:05:41,310 --> 02:05:42,710
Lucchesi,...

1208
02:05:42,722 --> 02:05:48,713
...will you please try and understand?
I have phoned him.

1209
02:05:48,962 --> 02:05:51,362
I have waited here by the phone.

1210
02:05:53,867 --> 02:05:58,500
<i>You would do well to remember, Mr. Lucchesi...</i>

1211
02:05:58,505 --> 02:06:03,799
...that this Pope has very different ideas...

1212
02:06:03,810 --> 02:06:05,778
...from the last one.

1213
02:06:27,333 --> 02:06:29,733
Good-bye, my old friend.

1214
02:06:31,438 --> 02:06:33,838
You could've lived a little longer.

1215
02:06:35,542 --> 02:06:38,443
I could be closer to my dream.

1216
02:06:44,350 --> 02:06:46,910
You were so loved, Don Tommasino.

1217
02:06:51,925 --> 02:06:55,827
Why was I so feared, and you so loved?

1218
02:06:56,930 --> 02:07:01,408
What was it?
I was no less honorable.

1219
02:07:03,803 --> 02:07:05,703
I wanted to do good.

1220
02:07:10,009 --> 02:07:12,910
What betrayed me?
My mind? My heart?

1221
02:07:15,949 --> 02:07:18,349
Why do I condemn myself so?

1222
02:07:24,858 --> 02:07:29,261
I swear on the lives of my children.

1223
02:07:33,567 --> 02:07:36,768
Give me a chance to redeem myself,...

1224
02:07:40,640 --> 02:07:44,542
...and I will sin no more.

1225
02:08:07,700 --> 02:08:12,703
You look pale. Bad news.
Tell me right away.

1226
02:08:14,274 --> 02:08:19,911
It's not just a bad banking deal.
These guys are butchers.

1227
02:08:21,114 --> 02:08:23,014
What guys?

1228
02:08:23,016 --> 02:08:27,109
Lucchesi. He controls all of them.

1229
02:08:27,220 --> 02:08:30,121
Altobello, the Archbishop,...

1230
02:08:31,224 --> 02:08:33,988
...other people higher up, P2, maybe.

1231
02:08:34,093 --> 02:08:37,961
Secret, unknown.
They're running things.

1232
02:08:40,867 --> 02:08:43,768
- I'm in their way.
- Yeah.

1233
02:08:43,870 --> 02:08:48,064
He's hired a professional assassin to kill you.
He's Sicilian.

1234
02:08:48,074 --> 02:08:52,577
I don't know his name.
They say he never fails.

1235
02:08:54,614 --> 02:08:56,514
Then no one is safe.

1236
02:08:59,552 --> 02:09:01,952
Even the new Pope is in danger.

1237
02:09:03,122 --> 02:09:07,124
No. We still have time. We can prevent this.

1238
02:09:11,564 --> 02:09:13,864
I tried Vincent.

1239
02:09:16,035 --> 02:09:21,038
I tried, to keep everything from coming to this.

1240
02:09:22,108 --> 02:09:27,202
But it's not possible. Not in this, world.

1241
02:09:28,214 --> 02:09:30,148
Give me the order.

1242
02:09:33,686 --> 02:09:35,586
You won't be able to go back.

1243
02:09:36,890 --> 02:09:40,018
- You'll be like me.
- Good.

1244
02:09:40,126 --> 02:09:45,862
All my life I wanted out. I wanted the family, out.

1245
02:09:47,400 --> 02:09:53,181
Well I don't want out.
I want the power to preserve the family.

1246
02:09:57,710 --> 02:09:59,610
I'm asking for the order.

1247
02:10:20,667 --> 02:10:26,267
- It's done.
- Because I can't do it anymore.

1248
02:10:30,143 --> 02:10:35,945
Well, it doesn't matter.
Vincent knows what to do. Come on outside.

1249
02:10:35,949 --> 02:10:39,475
Take a rest and -- and don't think about it.

1250
02:10:39,485 --> 02:10:45,585
- All I do is think about it.
- I'm your son. Command me in all things.

1251
02:10:48,161 --> 02:10:50,061
Give up my daughter.

1252
02:10:53,062 --> 02:10:59,132
That's the price you pay, for the life you choose.

1253
02:11:24,764 --> 02:11:30,564
Nephew, from this moment on,...

1254
02:11:32,272 --> 02:11:34,372
...call yourself Vincent Corleone.

1255
02:11:39,479 --> 02:11:40,878
Sit.

1256
02:13:44,579 --> 02:13:46,879
Et Tu, Vincenzo?

1257
02:13:46,973 --> 02:13:52,141
I know how you feel about Michael,
but you, you can't save him.

1258
02:13:52,145 --> 02:13:57,255
He's lost.
Think of yourself.

1259
02:13:58,551 --> 02:14:00,951
What's your answer, Vincent?

1260
02:14:03,156 --> 02:14:05,056
Enjoy the opera.

1261
02:14:07,093 --> 02:14:08,993
It's all taken care of.

1262
02:14:13,833 --> 02:14:16,333
You check the balcony.
I'll check the top fioor.

1263
02:14:20,540 --> 02:14:26,531
"Here's hoping Tony sings better at Theatre Maximo
than he does in the shower. Love, Douglas."

1264
02:14:27,713 --> 02:14:29,913
My darling, Constanzia.

1265
02:14:32,351 --> 02:14:35,251
- This is a great occasion. Yes.
- Come and sit down.

1266
02:14:39,859 --> 02:14:41,759
Happy birthday.

1267
02:14:41,861 --> 02:14:46,586
You're 80 years old, you don't look more than 60.
You're the only one who remembered.

1268
02:14:46,592 --> 02:14:51,998
Michael, we just got the word.
The Pope's ratifying the Immobiliare deal. We've won.

1269
02:14:52,004 --> 02:14:53,904
Congratulations.

1270
02:14:56,676 --> 02:14:59,076
How strange, the way things work.

1271
02:14:59,178 --> 02:15:02,679
The Pope's doing exactly what you said he'd do,
he's cleaning house.

1272
02:15:03,683 --> 02:15:08,745
Well, he should be careful.
It's dangerous to be an honest man.

1273
02:15:14,126 --> 02:15:16,926
I wanna put more muscle backstage with Tony.

1274
02:15:29,242 --> 02:15:34,753
- On your birthday, you used to shower me with treats.
- Tootsie Rolls!

1275
02:15:35,748 --> 02:15:41,387
The nuns who made these cannolis took
a vow of silence. They're the very finest.

1276
02:15:46,692 --> 02:15:52,691
- Hey, cuz.
- Where's your leather?

1277
02:15:56,369 --> 02:15:57,802
Stop it.

1278
02:16:03,676 --> 02:16:07,477
You're so thin.
You eat it.

1279
02:16:30,670 --> 02:16:35,273
It's over Mary. There are things I have to do
that you can't be a part of.

1280
02:16:35,274 --> 02:16:38,668
Don't look at your father,
it's not your father's decision, it's mine.

1281
02:16:40,112 --> 02:16:42,512
Don't hate your father.

1282
02:16:44,283 --> 02:16:48,417
There are things I'm going to be part of,
you can't be around.

1283
02:16:50,156 --> 02:16:54,956
- After tonight, you won't see me anymore.
- No.

1284
02:16:57,363 --> 02:17:00,159
You gotta understand,
Mary -- you gotta understand.

1285
02:17:01,934 --> 02:17:03,834
I'll always love you.

1286
02:17:16,749 --> 02:17:18,216
Love somebody else.

1287
02:17:41,006 --> 02:17:43,206
- To Tony.
- To Tony.

1288
02:20:59,538 --> 02:21:03,899
- They won't try anything.
- Yeah, everything is fine. It's all clear I think.

1289
02:21:03,909 --> 02:21:07,069
I've already sent Al Neri to the Vatican.

1290
02:23:56,381 --> 02:23:58,611
Check out the side.

1291
02:26:22,160 --> 02:26:25,061
Good. You got him.

1292
02:27:16,615 --> 02:27:19,415
<i>Tonight the Corleone family settles its accounts.</i>

1293
02:27:20,419 --> 02:27:26,023
<i>Keinszig -- that little Swiss banker fuck.</i>

1294
02:27:26,024 --> 02:27:30,788
<i>He's been swindling everyone from the beginning.
Fuck him.</i>

1295
02:27:31,630 --> 02:27:37,530
<i>Don Lucchesi. My friend.
Calo will pay him a visit at his home.</i>

1296
02:27:39,671 --> 02:27:42,872
<i>Neri, take a train to Rome.</i>

1297
02:27:44,643 --> 02:27:46,543
<i>Light a candle for the Archbishop.</i>

1298
02:29:49,935 --> 02:29:55,003
Michael, it's serious. Our man inside the
Vatican says there's a plot against the Pope.

1299
02:29:55,006 --> 02:29:57,567
You mean he's going to have a heart attack in the night.

1300
02:30:04,449 --> 02:30:09,452
This Pope has powerful enemies.
We may not be in time to save him.

1301
02:30:12,791 --> 02:30:14,290
Now let's go back to the opera.

1302
02:32:38,903 --> 02:32:43,281
Sleep. Sleep, Godfather.

1303
02:36:32,203 --> 02:36:34,698
- I like this opera.
- Yeah, I figured you would.

1304
02:36:34,706 --> 02:36:37,197
- Bravo. Say hello.
- Thank you.

1305
02:36:43,381 --> 02:36:45,611
- Did you like it?
- Great.

1306
02:36:47,452 --> 02:36:49,784
Let's get out of here.

1307
02:36:59,164 --> 02:37:03,230
- Can I please talk to you now?
- Not now Mary, it's not a good time.

1308
02:37:03,234 --> 02:37:07,236
- You're just like my father.
- Come on, stay with the family. Go on.

1309
02:37:08,473 --> 02:37:10,536
- Talk to me.
- The twins are dead.

1310
02:37:10,542 --> 02:37:14,544
<i>In about one minute, there's going to be
carabinieri crawling all over this place.</i>

1311
02:37:15,747 --> 02:37:18,407
- Okay. Let's get everybody to the cars, nice and quiet.
- Okay.

1312
02:37:18,416 --> 02:37:20,316
- Got it.
- Quiet.

1313
02:37:34,933 --> 02:37:38,227
When they hear the name Corleone,
they're going to think of a voice.

1314
02:37:47,979 --> 02:37:49,674
Dad.

1315
02:37:57,655 --> 02:37:59,122
This is my mom.

1316
02:38:08,499 --> 02:38:13,326
Dad? Why are you doing this to me.

1317
02:38:21,579 --> 02:38:25,115
- Go on, move back. Go on, move back.
- Hey, move!

1318
02:38:25,116 --> 02:38:31,013
- You don't have to do this to me, Please.
- Doing what? What do you mean?

1319
02:38:31,122 --> 02:38:32,814
Mary, please come...

1320
02:38:56,147 --> 02:38:57,605
Dad?

1321
02:39:14,834 --> 02:39:19,235
- No! Mary!
- Oh, God!

1322
02:39:19,241 --> 02:39:24,941
Oh, God, No! Oh, God, no, Please!

1323
02:39:26,778 --> 02:39:28,377
Mom, come on.

1324
02:39:45,930 --> 02:39:47,629
Let her go.

1325
02:39:52,704 --> 02:39:54,704
Let go.

